<p><ent>Savory</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Savory
<hw>Sa"vo*ry</hw> <pr>(s⟦amac⟧"v⟦osl⟧*r⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>savor⟦eacute⟧e</ets>; cf. It. <ets>santoreggia</ets>,
<ets>satureja</ets>, L. <ets>satureia</ets>,]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>An aromatic labiate plant (<spn>Satureia hortensis</spn>), much
used in cooking; -- also called <altname>summer savory</altname>.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>savoury</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Savoy</ent>⟦br⟧
